headlines.description: — Max Strus caught the pass, and with barely any time to think never mind shoot, one thing crossed his mind.
headlines.shortLinkText: Maxed out: Strus sinks 59-footer at the final horn, sending Cavaliers to 121-119 win over Mavericks

headlines.description: — The Orlando Magic didn't have their best player, but they did have the memory of two one-sided losses to the Brooklyn Nets to serve them Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Franz Wagner scores 21 points to lead Magic in 108-81 win over Nets

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Washington Wizards

headlines.description: — Klay Thompson was asked, again, how it feels to be coming off the bench after the Golden State Warriors improved to 6-1 over the past month in games he's entered as a reserve.
headlines.shortLinkText: Klay Thompson scores 25, Stephen Curry blanked in first half as Warriors beat Wizards 123-112

headlines.description: — Jalen Johnson had 22 points with 13 rebounds and the Atlanta Hawks never trailed after scoring the first 12 points and beat the Utah Jazz 124-97 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Johnson has 22 points as Hawks never trail in runaway 124-97 win over Jazz

headlines.description: — Celtics coach Joe Mazzulla doesn’t mind if his team struggles at times, if it learns and adapts along the way.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jaylen Brown scores 31, Celtics pull away in fourth to beat 76ers 117-99

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Trey Murphy III scored 26 points, Brandon Ingram had 24 and the New Orleans Pelicans beat the New York Knicks 115-92 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pelicans pull away in second half to beat injury-depleted Knicks 115-92

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 34 points, returning from an injury scare right before halftime, and the Minnesota Timberwolves beat the San Antonio Spurs 114-105 on Tuesday night without All-Star Karl-Anthony Towns.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards scores 34 as Wolves beat Spurs 114-105 without Towns

headlines.description: — Cade Cunningham was just glad the Detroit Pistons could take a deep breath and exhale. A rare win felt particularly good coming off such a heated loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cunningham scores 26 as Pistons beat Bulls 105-95 to stop 6-game slide

headlines.description: — The Milwaukee Bucks apparently just needed the All-Star break to discover how to play winning basketball under new coach Doc Rivers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks roll to 123-85 blowout of Hornets for their third consecutive victory

events.name: Houston Rockets at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 31 points and the Oklahoma City Thunder beat the Houston Rockets 112-95 on Tuesday night for their sixth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 31 as Thunder top Rockets 112-95 for 6th straight win

events.name: Miami Heat at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Jimmy Butler had 22 points and nine assists, Terry Rozier scored 19 points and the Miami Heat beat the Portland Trail Blazers 106-96 on Tuesday night for their fifth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Butler and Rozier make strong returns to the lineup, Heat beat Blazers 106-96
